-He's going to be OK.

04:32.901 --> 04:34.061
No, that's just storage.

04:34.925 --> 04:36.234
Uh...your room's upstairs.

04:36.949 --> 04:38.563
I'll show you.

04:57.148 --> 04:58.688
These are all my things.

04:59.109 --> 05:01.008
Yeah. Yeah, they are.

05:04.552 --> 05:06.015
What else do you remember?

05:07.336 --> 05:08.896
I don't know
if I can keep doing this.

05:09.515 --> 05:10.783
Doing what?

05:12.751 --> 05:14.577
Telling you how I feel.

05:15.347 --> 05:16.257
Why?

05:18.283 --> 05:21.736
Honestly, I still feel
uncomfortable calling you 'Dad'.

05:30.466 --> 05:31.661
You're gonna be OK.

05:32.842 --> 05:34.654
I think we're all gonna be OK.

05:36.839 --> 05:39.145
We all just want you
to be happy and...

05:39.471 --> 05:42.065
Please...
Hey, I just...you're here now...

05:42.403 --> 05:43.805
This is your home.

05:45.305 --> 05:48.003
I know it can't be
easy starting your life over.

05:48.339 --> 05:51.572
New home, new wife, new kids.
You seem to be doing just fine

06:05.904 --> 06:07.484
I need you to take
 those twice a day.

06:08.770 --> 06:10.330
You just got out of the hospital.

06:10.689 --> 06:12.196
Doesn't come without
side effects.

06:13.850 --> 06:15.063
What if I forget?

06:16.865 --> 06:17.596
Don't.

08:00.790 --> 08:02.172
Hey...Don't cry.

08:06.969 --> 08:08.505
I remember everything.

08:08.993 --> 08:12.799
But...I just can't feel it.

08:13.600 --> 08:15.824
I know that doesn't make any sense.
But...

08:19.413 --> 08:22.308
I mean, my head hurts sometimes
when I think about that stuff.

08:29.345 --> 08:30.933
She smiles when she's
with you.

08:32.255 --> 08:33.565
My sister.

08:35.198 --> 08:36.756
She used to be that
way all the time.

08:43.788 --> 08:44.762
You scared?

08:47.024 --> 08:47.809
No.

08:50.675 --> 08:52.675
You know I had
almost forgotten about it?

08:55.062 --> 08:55.967
Sorry.

09:06.430 --> 09:08.735
Call me when you get there.
-Mom, please.

09:31.081 --> 09:32.726
You know you're my
best friend, right?

09:45.890 --> 09:47.890
-I gotta go.
-OK.

10:12.205 --> 10:15.352
I can't believe we're
not going to see him for seven months.

10:20.467 --> 10:22.467
Why did you
go to the airport?

10:23.381 --> 10:24.454
Why?

10:24.755 --> 10:27.756
I was just curious. Jesus.

10:28.656 --> 10:29.696
That picture.

10:35.201 --> 10:36.705
I don't know who it is.

10:37.861 --> 10:38.819
You?

10:40.513 --> 10:41.274
No.

10:49.115 --> 10:50.188
By the way,

10:50.941 --> 10:52.871
mom wanted you to
have dinner with her tomorrow night.

10:52.903 --> 10:54.350
Are you? 
-I live there.

10:54.911 --> 10:56.495
It's your turn to
deal with her shit.

11:00.615 --> 11:01.609
Hey Ally.

11:06.039 --> 11:07.189
Who's in the picture?

11:11.318 --> 11:12.524
Why do you have
to do that?

11:15.566 --> 11:16.533
What?

11:17.726 --> 11:19.706
I hate it when you do this.

11:20.465 --> 11:22.418
This is not exactly been easy.

11:23.484 --> 11:25.184
Will you quit trying
to blame me?

11:25.589 --> 11:26.484
Or Ally?

11:26.916 --> 11:27.779
I don't.

11:28.572 --> 11:31.105
I don't. 
I blame your father.

11:31.519 --> 11:32.226
Oh, Jesus...

11:33.099 --> 11:36.589
Can we have one dinner without
you digging his grave, too?

11:36.614 --> 11:39.941
He did that himself.
You have no idea what it is like to

11:39.966 --> 11:42.014
love someone for twenty years

11:42.157 --> 11:46.317
And then watch them turn
and marry the next best thing.

11:47.071 --> 11:51.977
It was his responsibility to help us
through everything and...

11:52.415 --> 11:55.241
...and he let this family fall apart.

11:57.812 --> 11:59.399
Let me tell you something, Ethan.

12:00.144 --> 12:01.332
Look at me!

12:04.600 --> 12:05.995
Love makes you blind.

13:05.806 --> 13:06.921
Excuse me, miss.

13:06.946 --> 13:09.179
Uh, you dropped this.

16:16.058 --> 16:17.239
What are you doing?

16:21.279 --> 16:22.546
I thought you were asleep.

16:22.571 --> 16:23.059
Oh,

16:24.258 --> 16:26.856
what do you possibly think you're
going to find here, Ethan, huh?

16:28.410 --> 16:29.717
What happened to me?

16:30.423 --> 16:32.123
We saved your life, Ethan.

16:32.539 --> 16:35.715
I know you keep saying that, but
I really think I'm OK.

16:37.822 --> 16:39.075
I just need to know.

16:40.770 --> 16:43.038
Well, there are some
things I can't tell you.

16:44.214 --> 16:46.694
Understanding it is with a
doctor-patient relationship.

16:46.956 --> 16:48.761
What about a father-son relationship?

16:49.759 --> 16:50.782
I can't.

16:58.036 --> 16:59.192
I'm sorry.

17:01.118 --> 17:02.774
Don't come here ever again.

18:46.738 --> 18:48.138
Are you sure it was her?

18:49.028 --> 18:49.892
Yeah.

18:50.443 --> 18:51.908
Well, what'd she say?

18:53.534 --> 18:55.003
Didn't ask.

18:56.272 --> 18:57.327
Why not?

18:59.446 --> 19:01.166
Ally, I followed her.

19:01.383 --> 19:04.316
-I never done that before.
-How do you know?

19:05.316 --> 19:06.543
My memory's fine.

19:06.843 --> 19:09.125
It's-it's not like I
don't remember stuff.

19:10.636 --> 19:12.362
Like when I gave you that.

19:18.523 --> 19:20.363
If you know something,

19:21.446 --> 19:22.855
I wish you'd tell me.

19:24.513 --> 19:27.116
I wish you didn't
believe I had something to hide.

19:32.901 --> 19:33.916
OK.

19:38.176 --> 19:39.596
Have you talked to Luke?

19:39.907 --> 19:41.019
No.

19:42.491 --> 19:43.518
I miss him.

19:45.317 --> 19:46.790
I think I'm gonna go.

19:47.980 --> 19:49.029
Ethan...

19:52.341 --> 19:53.417
Our family...

19:55.752 --> 19:57.702
You're the only one
who still wants it.

19:59.636 --> 20:02.155
Let's not let that 
get between us.

20:13.928 --> 20:15.070
Shut up.

20:15.600 --> 20:18.103
Seriously? Are you really
going to bring me here? Seriously?

20:41.980 --> 20:42.714
Hi.

20:42.739 --> 20:44.134
You're Camille, right?

20:44.891 --> 20:46.334
What is it with you?

20:50.522 --> 20:51.733
What do you mean?

20:53.402 --> 20:54.943
You're stalking me.

20:57.387 --> 20:59.387
I think you're giving yourself
too much credit.

21:03.058 --> 21:04.991
No, I'm not.

21:13.999 --> 21:15.013
OK.

21:16.545 --> 21:17.621
Forget it.

21:19.135 --> 21:20.813
Sit down, Ethan.

21:22.278 --> 21:23.985
I was just kidding.

21:25.380 --> 21:27.005
How'd you know my name?

21:30.217 --> 21:32.006
Everyone knows your name.

21:44.826 --> 21:46.780
Hey, Ethan. What a
pleasant surprise.

21:46.898 --> 21:49.023
Hey, Miss Linda. 
You got a minute?

21:50.642 --> 21:51.942
Do you know Camille?

21:52.250 --> 21:54.041
I don't know. 
Maybe.

21:55.521 --> 21:56.681
Do you remember this?

21:57.757 --> 21:58.810
Look.

22:14.241 --> 22:15.561
Who's that?

22:16.637 --> 22:17.986
I don't remember that.

22:20.042 --> 22:21.153
Ethan...

22:24.726 --> 22:26.726
That...is your brother.

22:28.156 --> 22:29.507
Adam.

22:34.384 --> 22:35.686
My brother?

22:38.526 --> 22:41.555
I don't remember that,
I don't have any memory.

22:42.301 --> 22:44.053
Memory of that.

22:46.735 --> 22:48.994
Do you have anything else
about that?

22:49.563 --> 22:50.627
Ethan...

22:53.159 --> 22:56.821
I'm sure it will come back to you. 
Just give it some time.

22:58.195 --> 23:00.068
I've been told that before.

23:01.083 --> 23:02.148
Ethan.

23:05.276 --> 23:06.544
Where is he?

23:14.928 --> 23:16.716
Adam Galloway. 
I'm here to see him.

23:16.741 --> 23:19.159
I'm sorry, Ethan, you're not
 authorized to go up there.

23:19.937 --> 23:21.349
You know my name!

23:21.374 --> 23:23.039
Everyone here knows your name.

23:23.127 --> 23:25.688
You're Charles' son. 
Would you  like me to call him for you?

23:26.191 --> 23:27.737
Ethan, you can't go!

23:27.762 --> 23:28.764
Ethan!

23:32.846 --> 23:34.224
I know I have a brother!

23:34.528 --> 23:36.128
Why didn't you tell me?
Where is he?

23:36.153 --> 23:38.466
Ethan, Ethan...whoa.
Calm down, take a breath.

23:38.753 --> 23:41.246
Take a breath.
Take a breath. OK.

23:44.653 --> 23:46.106
Listen, listen...listen to me,

23:46.380 --> 23:47.371
your brother...

23:47.973 --> 23:50.119
Hey, your brother
Adam died.

23:50.716 --> 23:52.456
Your brother's dead, Ethan.

23:52.716 --> 23:55.176
Yeah. He killed himself
a little over a year ago.

23:55.470 --> 23:57.061
Let's go. 
It's going to be OK.

23:57.494 --> 23:59.215
It's going to be OK. 
Yes.

24:01.506 --> 24:03.905
It's going to be OK. Whoa,
whoa, whoa.

24:08.040 --> 24:09.058
Ethan.

24:12.862 --> 24:14.361
Ethan, you're alright.

24:16.131 --> 24:17.138
Hey! Hey.

24:17.441 --> 24:19.904
You're alright. 
You're alright.

24:26.302 --> 24:27.602
Say something.

24:29.821 --> 24:30.889
Say something.

24:31.402 --> 24:32.296
Come on.

24:32.709 --> 24:34.494
Why did she tell me that?

24:35.094 --> 24:36.921
Who told you what? 
Who?

24:38.631 --> 24:40.199
Lucas' mom.

24:40.816 --> 24:44.452
Why did she tell me?
-No, no. No. Ethan. You heard wrong.

24:45.095 --> 24:46.813
You heard wrong.

24:48.751 --> 24:50.594
No, you're alright.

24:52.605 --> 24:53.898
Let's get you home.

24:54.192 --> 24:55.671
I'm going to get you home, Ok?

24:56.216 --> 24:57.151
Ok.

25:02.365 --> 25:03.845
Come on, I got you.

25:05.111 --> 25:06.752
I'm going to get you home.

25:07.544 --> 25:08.919
You're gonna be alright.

25:09.126 --> 25:10.265
You're alright.

25:27.709 --> 25:29.151
What are those?

25:30.526 --> 25:31.918
What are you doing here?

25:33.496 --> 25:35.157
Your step-mom let me in.

25:35.520 --> 25:37.397
-She did?
-Uh-hum

25:39.625 --> 25:40.594
Excuse me.
Oh.

25:41.364 --> 25:43.160
Sorry. 
Please.

25:57.116 --> 25:59.116
It's a little cleaner 
than I remembered.

25:59.453 --> 26:01.380
You've never been in
my room before.

26:02.234 --> 26:03.307
Have you?

26:04.507 --> 26:08.320
Uh...It's a little cleaner
than I would have thought.

26:11.472 --> 26:12.940
What are you doing here?

26:17.194 --> 26:18.252
Ok...

26:18.992 --> 26:21.966
I...came to say I'm sorry.

26:22.824 --> 26:24.253
About yesterday.

26:26.475 --> 26:27.488
I'm...

26:28.554 --> 26:30.314
I'm sorry.

26:33.728 --> 26:34.753
Ok.

26:39.804 --> 26:41.694
So, you paint?

26:42.846 --> 26:43.854
No.

26:45.549 --> 26:46.995
Who did these?

26:47.939 --> 26:49.497
You ask a lot of questions.

26:50.309 --> 26:52.409
They're really beautiful, Ethan.

26:52.890 --> 26:54.693
I mess around sometimes.

26:56.714 --> 26:58.880
How come they don't have faces?

27:00.184 --> 27:01.546
I can't do faces.

27:03.943 --> 27:06.756
Have you ever read 
the poem Bellustar?

27:08.022 --> 27:10.485
I'm at the adapted play
tomorrow night.

27:10.966 --> 27:12.299
You should come.

27:12.990 --> 27:15.020
I believe you know where it is.

27:16.145 --> 27:17.147
Right.

27:18.408 --> 27:20.663
You know, you're supposed
to stand eight feet away.

27:20.840 --> 27:21.820
Hmm.

27:22.209 --> 27:24.284
So, there's a goddess in the poem

27:24.785 --> 27:26.904
also faceless. 
Laughing.

27:27.738 --> 27:30.371
My first poem 
you can't even see my face.

